-- Tokyo Electron, Sharp to tie up in solar cells
-- 
-- Sun Feb 17, 2008 7:26pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/02/18/us-sharp-tokyo-electron-solar-idUSTFA00299320080218

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Japan's Tokyo Electron Ltd ( 8035.T ), the world's No. 2 maker of semiconductor equipment, said on Monday it was planning an alliance with consumer electronics and panel maker Sharp Corp ( 6753.T ) in the solar cell market. 

 An announcement would come later in the day, Tokyo Electron said. (Reporting by  Mayumi Negishi )